==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expectoration
<hw>Ex*pec`to*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>expectoration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of ejecting
phlegm or mucus from the throat or lungs, by coughing, hawking, and
spitting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is expectorated, as phlegm or
mucus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expectorative</ent>⟦br⟧
